1
00:00:24,810 --> 00:00:26,641
Bjorling...

2
00:00:27,313 --> 00:00:28,975
Suliotis?

3
00:00:29,649 --> 00:00:31,810
Almost. Bjorling is easy.

4
00:00:38,993 --> 00:00:40,654
Tebaldi?

5
00:00:40,728 --> 00:00:42,992
Bingo!

6
00:00:43,064 --> 00:00:45,226
It's my turn now.

7
00:00:50,072 --> 00:00:52,633
- Don't look!
- But I'm not looking.

8
00:00:52,709 --> 00:00:54,199
Did Daddy look?

9
00:00:54,877 --> 00:00:56,367
Is that true?

10
00:01:09,294 --> 00:01:10,955
Oh, God!

11
00:01:12,731 --> 00:01:14,393
Gigli!

12
00:01:14,467 --> 00:01:17,402
That's obvious!
But what's the piece?

13
00:01:30,551 --> 00:01:31,882
Never heard it!

14
00:01:31,953 --> 00:01:33,614
Is it new?

15
00:01:34,455 --> 00:01:36,116
Seems to be.

16
00:01:37,292 --> 00:01:38,953
Well, darling?

17
00:01:47,137 --> 00:01:49,071
I'd say Handel.

18
00:01:49,139 --> 00:01:51,505
Right. But what is it?

19
00:01:54,178 --> 00:01:56,009
No idea!

20
00:02:02,554 --> 00:02:03,543
Well?

21
00:02:03,622 --> 00:02:05,954
I give up. What is it?

22
00:02:06,024 --> 00:02:07,822
Three-two to me!

23
00:02:10,830 --> 00:02:13,060
So, what is it?

24
00:02:13,900 --> 00:02:15,390
Now get your hands off!

25
00:02:15,469 --> 00:02:17,403
Just listen!

26
00:03:44,335 --> 00:03:46,166
That's cheating!

27
00:03:46,237 --> 00:03:47,227
Sorry?

28
00:03:47,306 --> 00:03:49,297
It's cheating to be practicing.

29
00:03:49,375 --> 00:03:52,538
We've booked for 10:00
tomorrow morning. You are coming?

30
00:03:53,712 --> 00:03:54,941
Yes, sure.

31
00:04:00,353 --> 00:04:01,945
We'll put the boat in the water first.

32
00:04:02,623 --> 00:04:05,956
Can you give us a hand?
Let's say, in 20 minutes?

33
00:04:09,797 --> 00:04:12,232
Sure! Yes, I'll be there in 20 minutes.

34
00:04:12,301 --> 00:04:14,132
Okay. Thanks.

35
00:04:14,202 --> 00:04:15,692
See you in a tick.

36
00:04:24,981 --> 00:04:26,813
What's up with him?

37
00:04:26,884 --> 00:04:28,044
No idea.

38
00:04:28,118 --> 00:04:29,608
He seems in a huff.

39
00:04:29,687 --> 00:04:31,848
She didn't say a word.

40
00:04:31,922 --> 00:04:34,084
Who did you arrange
to play with tomorrow?

41
00:04:34,159 --> 00:04:35,490
Her.

42
00:04:35,560 --> 00:04:36,925
Yesterday?

43
00:04:36,995 --> 00:04:38,656
The day before.

44
00:04:38,730 --> 00:04:39,662
Well?

45
00:04:40,499 --> 00:04:42,160
Nothing. She was totally normal.

46
00:04:42,234 --> 00:04:44,566
Sissi isn't there.

47
00:04:44,637 --> 00:04:47,629
Maybe she was just in the house.
Or at the beach.

48
00:04:49,509 --> 00:04:51,477
Who were the two laddies?

49
00:04:52,145 --> 00:04:53,305
How should I know?

50
00:04:53,380 --> 00:04:57,317
They're probably relatives.
I think his brother has a son that age.

51
00:05:33,826 --> 00:05:36,818
Don't put that there!
Take your things upstairs!

52
00:05:36,896 --> 00:05:37,885
Okay.

53
00:05:37,964 --> 00:05:39,295
Do it now!

54
00:05:39,365 --> 00:05:42,199
Don't leave things in the entrance,
or someone will trip over.

55
00:05:42,269 --> 00:05:45,761
There's still so much left in the car.

56
00:05:45,839 --> 00:05:47,830
Are you listening?

57
00:05:47,908 --> 00:05:49,774
I'm going!

58
00:05:50,278 --> 00:05:53,270
Open the windows, will you.
We need to let some air in.

59
00:05:53,348 --> 00:05:55,282
Okay, Mom!

60
00:06:02,291 --> 00:06:04,886
Stop it, Rolfi! Stop it!

61
00:06:04,961 --> 00:06:06,792
Go on, get down!

62
00:06:06,863 --> 00:06:08,728
I have to unpack!

63
00:06:09,966 --> 00:06:11,831
Go on, get out!

64
00:06:13,838 --> 00:06:15,806
- Georg?
- Yes?

65
00:06:15,873 --> 00:06:17,738
Where's the other box
with the food?

66
00:06:18,910 --> 00:06:20,242
I'll bring it right away.

67
00:06:20,312 --> 00:06:23,338
The golf gear was in the way.
I put it in the Rover last.

68
00:06:24,717 --> 00:06:29,451
We'd better get them in quick!
The things have got really hot!

69
00:06:29,522 --> 00:06:32,514
This cool-box is totally useless.

70
00:06:32,592 --> 00:06:35,756
Stop it now, you'll knock me over.

71
00:06:35,830 --> 00:06:37,559
- The butter's all soft.
- Go see your mistress.

72
00:06:38,566 --> 00:06:40,898
There're some cold cuts in the other box.

73
00:06:40,968 --> 00:06:43,096
I'll get it. I'll just open the windows.

74
00:06:45,273 --> 00:06:48,606
Leave the shutters closed on the lake side,
or it'll be too hot.

75
00:06:48,677 --> 00:06:50,397
Stop that. You'll get something

76
00:06:50,398 --> 00:06:52,671
in a minute, I must just put this away.

77
00:06:52,749 --> 00:06:56,913
Can't you call the dog?
He won't let me put the things away.

78
00:06:57,019 --> 00:06:58,419
Rolfi!

79
00:06:58,455 --> 00:06:59,513
Come here!

80
00:06:59,590 --> 00:07:00,750
Come and see your master!

81
00:07:00,824 --> 00:07:04,658
And the bottles too,
otherwise it'll all be warm by the evening.

82
00:07:08,333 --> 00:07:09,994
Stop it, Rolfi!

83
00:07:10,068 --> 00:07:11,558
Be quiet!

84
00:07:12,303 --> 00:07:13,794
Come in!

85
00:07:14,707 --> 00:07:16,800
Sorry. He's off his head.

86
00:07:16,876 --> 00:07:18,366
Come in!

87
00:07:19,378 --> 00:07:20,641
Hello.

88
00:07:20,714 --> 00:07:23,547
Thanks for coming.
It'd have been tough on our own.

89
00:07:23,617 --> 00:07:26,450
- No problem! This is...
- Paul. Nice to meet you.

90
00:07:26,520 --> 00:07:28,250
Paul is son of a business colleague.

91
00:07:28,322 --> 00:07:31,655
- It's a pleasure. Nice of you to help.
- Mine too.

92
00:07:31,726 --> 00:07:33,387
I mean, the pleasure's mine.

93
00:07:34,562 --> 00:07:37,623
- Not so much his.
- Will you be quiet?

94
00:07:37,699 --> 00:07:38,859
Lunatic!

95
00:07:38,934 --> 00:07:41,402
- Get into the house, go on!
- Come here, Rolfi!

96
00:07:42,404 --> 00:07:44,703
- When did you get out here?
- Last week.

97
00:07:45,208 --> 00:07:46,038
You too?

98
00:07:46,109 --> 00:07:47,542
- Yes.
- No.

99
00:07:47,610 --> 00:07:50,340
They didn't arrive till the weekend.
We came on Friday.

100
00:07:52,183 --> 00:07:53,514
Hello, Fred!

101
00:07:53,584 --> 00:07:55,677
Nice of you to come over right away.

102
00:07:57,688 --> 00:08:00,180
- How's Eva?
- Fine.

103
00:08:01,059 --> 00:08:02,720
- Hello.
- Hello, madam.

104
00:08:03,762 --> 00:08:05,252
...and where's Tropea?

105
00:08:05,330 --> 00:08:07,390
In south Italy. Right at the tip,

106
00:08:07,466 --> 00:08:10,458
- almost on the toes of the boot.
- But it's even hotter there.

107
00:08:10,536 --> 00:08:12,197
Not necessarily.

108
00:08:12,271 --> 00:08:14,585
Last year when I was in Italy it was freezing

109
00:08:14,586 --> 00:08:16,436
and here you were swimming, right?

110
00:08:16,510 --> 00:08:20,310
But it's a shame Sissi isn't here.
Without her, it's...

111
00:08:20,981 --> 00:08:22,711
- Be careful!
- I am!

112
00:08:22,784 --> 00:08:25,116
Careful, or the overhauling
will have been for nothing.

113
00:08:25,186 --> 00:08:27,177
Look, you can't see anything!

114
00:08:27,255 --> 00:08:28,244
Good.

115
00:08:29,258 --> 00:08:31,283
Can you help me lift the boom over?

116
00:08:35,164 --> 00:08:36,654
Mind the halyard!

117
00:08:51,015 --> 00:08:54,008
But she said she'd be there
for the whole holiday.

118
00:08:54,086 --> 00:08:58,250
Listen, my boy.
I don't know why she isn't there either.

119
00:08:58,357 --> 00:09:01,850
Maybe she went to Tropea
with a school friend. I don't know.

120
00:09:01,895 --> 00:09:05,228
Tomorrow we'll go over and ask
her mother. She's bound to explain all.

121
00:09:05,298 --> 00:09:06,959
Now stop moping...

122
00:09:07,033 --> 00:09:09,195
Why was Uncle Fred so strange?

123
00:09:09,270 --> 00:09:11,431
I'm not surprised!

124
00:09:11,505 --> 00:09:14,099
She got pretty worked up
about it last time.

125
00:09:14,775 --> 00:09:16,471
Forget it, please.

126
00:09:17,712 --> 00:09:20,408
She won't change,
and you'll just get in a state.

127
00:09:21,249 --> 00:09:22,511
Exactly!

128
00:09:23,185 --> 00:09:24,880
That's it!

129
00:09:26,389 --> 00:09:28,880
Great. They're outside
working on the boat.

130
00:09:31,328 --> 00:09:32,659
What?

131
00:09:33,797 --> 00:09:36,630
5:00 or 5:30.
I don't know the time here,

132
00:09:36,700 --> 00:09:38,532
I mean, the kitchen clock has stopped.

133
00:09:38,603 --> 00:09:40,798
I must get a new battery on Monday.

134
00:09:42,740 --> 00:09:44,071
What?

135
00:09:44,142 --> 00:09:45,906
Yes, that's what I'm doing now.

136
00:09:46,645 --> 00:09:48,374
Some fillets.

137
00:09:49,214 --> 00:09:51,279
Yes, you know, it's crazy. The whole thing

138
00:09:51,280 --> 00:09:53,049
defrosted and now it needs eating.

139
00:09:53,954 --> 00:09:55,945
Come out and see us!

140
00:09:56,022 --> 00:10:00,015
No, really, like a fool, I froze
three pounds of beef fillet at once,

141
00:10:00,093 --> 00:10:02,255
and now here I am.

142
00:10:02,330 --> 00:10:05,891
No, I'm not joking.
Come and spend the weekend.

143
00:10:06,734 --> 00:10:07,666
What?

144
00:10:07,735 --> 00:10:10,204
He shouldn't make such a fuss.
Hold on.

145
00:10:10,872 --> 00:10:13,033
We need a sharp knife.

146
00:10:16,579 --> 00:10:18,638
I'd like to see it again some day.
Tell Dad.

147
00:10:18,715 --> 00:10:20,046
Sorry.

148
00:10:20,116 --> 00:10:22,607
Tell your beloved to pack up his laptop,

149
00:10:22,685 --> 00:10:25,849
get in the car, and you'll be here
in two hours at the most!

150
00:10:27,791 --> 00:10:29,656
He shouldn't be so elusive.

151
00:10:31,262 --> 00:10:32,923
Okay. Think about it.

152
00:10:32,998 --> 00:10:35,398
In any case,
there's enough steak here for a week.

153
00:10:37,435 --> 00:10:38,595
Bye, Fanny.

154
00:10:38,670 --> 00:10:40,832
Say, give us another ring anyway

155
00:10:40,906 --> 00:10:43,500
to tell us whether we can expect you.

156
00:10:43,576 --> 00:10:45,066
Yes, bye.

157
00:10:45,144 --> 00:10:47,443
- What is it now?
- Someone's here.

158
00:10:47,514 --> 00:10:49,448
- Where?
- At the door.

159
00:10:54,021 --> 00:10:54,954
Hello?

160
00:10:55,023 --> 00:10:57,150
Hello. Sorry to disturb you.

161
00:10:57,258 --> 00:10:58,748
I'm from next door.

162
00:10:58,793 --> 00:11:01,729
We saw each other
when you stopped the car at the gate.

163
00:11:01,797 --> 00:11:03,458
Oh, yes, we did.

164
00:11:04,600 --> 00:11:06,261
Come in, please.

165
00:11:07,436 --> 00:11:10,099
Hurry up, we're eating in 10 minutes!

166
00:11:10,173 --> 00:11:11,663
So what is it?

167
00:11:11,741 --> 00:11:13,231
Well...

168
00:11:13,309 --> 00:11:14,970
Eva sent...

169
00:11:15,045 --> 00:11:17,037
I mean, Mrs. Berlinger sent me.

170
00:11:17,114 --> 00:11:18,604
She's just cooking...

171
00:11:19,350 --> 00:11:23,650
and she's run out of eggs.
She wonders if you can help her out.

172
00:11:23,721 --> 00:11:25,485
But of course.

173
00:11:25,557 --> 00:11:27,286
- How many does she need?
- Four.

174
00:11:28,026 --> 00:11:29,015
Four?

175
00:11:29,728 --> 00:11:32,026
- What for?
- Sorry?

176
00:11:32,097 --> 00:11:33,588
What for?

177
00:11:33,666 --> 00:11:35,657
What does she need the eggs for?

178
00:11:35,735 --> 00:11:37,396
I mean, what's she making?

179
00:11:37,470 --> 00:11:39,461
No idea.

180
00:11:40,207 --> 00:11:42,368
Are they okay like that
or shall I wrap them?

181
00:11:43,043 --> 00:11:44,533
As you like.

182
00:11:45,212 --> 00:11:47,043
So how did you get in?

183
00:11:47,114 --> 00:11:49,606
At the front.
I mean, by the beach.

184
00:11:49,684 --> 00:11:51,845
But you didn't get wet at all!

185
00:11:51,920 --> 00:11:53,410
There's a hole in the fence,

186
00:11:53,488 --> 00:11:54,978
by the water, not in the water.

187
00:11:55,057 --> 00:11:56,251
Fred knows -

188
00:11:56,325 --> 00:11:59,590
I mean, Mr. Berlinger knows it.
He showed me it.

189
00:11:59,695 --> 00:12:01,026
I see. Okay.

190
00:12:01,063 --> 00:12:02,725
So, wrapped, or is this okay?

191
00:12:02,799 --> 00:12:04,733
No, no, that's fine, no problem.

192
00:12:04,801 --> 00:12:06,769
- Many thanks.
- You're welcome.

193
00:12:09,673 --> 00:12:12,165
Love to Eva.
Look forward to the golf tomorrow!

194
00:12:12,243 --> 00:12:14,108
I'll tell her. Thanks again.

195
00:12:14,178 --> 00:12:16,669
And thanks again to Fred
and your friend -

196
00:12:16,747 --> 00:12:19,239
- Damn it!
- What's up?

197
00:12:25,390 --> 00:12:26,881
It's not a disaster.

198
00:12:26,960 --> 00:12:28,621
Hang on.

199
00:12:42,911 --> 00:12:44,970
Thank God, we just arrived...

200
00:12:45,647 --> 00:12:48,309
and I must shop
in the village on Monday.

201
00:12:48,383 --> 00:12:49,942
I'm really embarrassed.

202
00:12:50,019 --> 00:12:53,511
It's nothing. No one here eats eggs
for breakfast anyway,

203
00:12:53,589 --> 00:12:55,580
so it's not a major problem.

204
00:12:55,658 --> 00:12:57,593
That's a relief, thank you.

205
00:12:58,762 --> 00:13:01,253
I should just have been more careful.

206
00:13:02,232 --> 00:13:05,930
- I put my left hand -
- Well, no point in crying over spilt milk.

207
00:13:06,004 --> 00:13:07,335
You're really kind.

208
00:13:07,405 --> 00:13:09,168
One does one's best.

209
00:13:17,149 --> 00:13:18,639
I'm really sorry.

210
00:13:22,889 --> 00:13:24,584
I'm very clumsy, you know.

211
00:13:25,926 --> 00:13:28,361
I think I've got two left hands.

212
00:13:28,429 --> 00:13:30,761
So you're ideal for carrying eggs.

213
00:13:30,831 --> 00:13:32,765
Yes, you could say.

214
00:13:34,269 --> 00:13:36,032
Well...

215
00:13:36,104 --> 00:13:38,572
And what are we going to do now?

216
00:13:42,579 --> 00:13:46,242
We do have steak,
but we might be getting visitors,

217
00:13:46,316 --> 00:13:48,750
and they're bound to want eggs
for breakfast.

218
00:13:49,587 --> 00:13:51,782
But you'll have four left.

219
00:13:54,291 --> 00:13:57,284
After all, I did see
you had a box of twelve, right?

220
00:13:58,430 --> 00:14:00,762
You're right.

221
00:14:14,881 --> 00:14:16,542
Shouldn't I wrap them up?

222
00:14:16,617 --> 00:14:18,278
No need.

223
00:14:18,352 --> 00:14:19,512
Are you sure?

224
00:14:19,586 --> 00:14:21,418
If you want to.

225
00:14:21,489 --> 00:14:23,150
If I want to?

226
00:14:23,224 --> 00:14:25,283
Well, maybe it is better after all.

227
00:14:28,264 --> 00:14:30,596
- Oh, no!
- What's the matter?

228
00:14:32,768 --> 00:14:34,429
Oh, no!

229
00:15:06,707 --> 00:15:08,197
I'm sorry.

230
00:15:09,710 --> 00:15:12,179
Before you destroy the rest of the kitchen,

231
00:15:12,180 --> 00:15:14,705
maybe you should take your eggs and leave.

232
00:15:16,551 --> 00:15:18,041
Well...

233
00:15:22,058 --> 00:15:23,889
Here you are.

234
00:15:23,959 --> 00:15:25,551
Won't you wrap them?

235
00:15:42,413 --> 00:15:44,678
I'm really sorry.

236
00:15:45,517 --> 00:15:47,007
Honestly.

237
00:15:47,086 --> 00:15:48,576
Me too.

238
00:15:55,328 --> 00:15:56,556
There.

239
00:15:56,629 --> 00:15:59,292
- Here you are.
- Many thanks. Thank you.

240
00:15:59,400 --> 00:16:01,334
I'll tell Mrs. Berlinger how nice you were.

241
00:16:01,369 --> 00:16:03,462
Okay. Do as you see fit.

242
00:16:03,537 --> 00:16:05,698
- Bye.
- Good-bye.

243
00:17:09,546 --> 00:17:11,207
Excuse me?

244
00:17:21,725 --> 00:17:23,057
Stop it! Rolfi!

245
00:17:23,128 --> 00:17:24,618
Excuse me!

246
00:17:26,398 --> 00:17:28,366
Off you go!

247
00:17:28,433 --> 00:17:30,094
Get lost!

248
00:17:30,168 --> 00:17:32,000
I mean now!

249
00:17:35,074 --> 00:17:37,941
I'm sorry. He's completely harmless.

250
00:17:38,010 --> 00:17:40,502
- He just wants to have a game.
- Funny game.

251
00:17:41,181 --> 00:17:42,842
Did he hurt you?

252
00:17:42,916 --> 00:17:44,577
Peter's just afraid of dogs.

253
00:17:44,651 --> 00:17:46,847
- I'm sorry.
- Me too.

254
00:17:46,921 --> 00:17:48,912
He jumped up on me.

255
00:17:48,990 --> 00:17:50,651
I'm sorry about that.

256
00:17:50,725 --> 00:17:52,386
Well.

257
00:17:52,460 --> 00:17:54,452
Shall I lock him in so you can leave?

258
00:17:54,530 --> 00:17:56,555
- No need.
- I can tell my husband to -

259
00:17:56,632 --> 00:17:58,623
There's really no need, thanks.

260
00:17:58,734 --> 00:18:01,397
It's my fault.
I quite forgot the dog.

261
00:18:01,438 --> 00:18:03,599
Otherwise, I'd have come to fetch the...

262
00:18:04,341 --> 00:18:06,002
Oh! What a wonderful kit!

263
00:18:06,076 --> 00:18:07,737
Gallaway, isn't it?

264
00:18:10,982 --> 00:18:12,643
It's fantastic.

265
00:18:12,717 --> 00:18:14,275
May I?

266
00:18:15,152 --> 00:18:17,519
We hardly stand a chance for tomorrow!

267
00:18:19,358 --> 00:18:21,155
Good clubs don't make good golfers.

268
00:18:21,827 --> 00:18:23,488
That's true, yes.

269
00:18:25,164 --> 00:18:28,065
Would it be cheeky of me
to ask if I can try it just once?

270
00:18:29,068 --> 00:18:31,229
Right now, outside?

271
00:18:31,304 --> 00:18:32,567
Please! Okay?

272
00:18:32,640 --> 00:18:34,631
From the lawn out to the lake, okay?

273
00:18:36,510 --> 00:18:38,341
- If it makes you happy. I -
- Thanks.

274
00:18:43,618 --> 00:18:45,108
Excuse me.

275
00:18:45,687 --> 00:18:47,519
He loves golf!

276
00:18:47,590 --> 00:18:49,558
- We both do.
- Sorry?

277
00:18:49,625 --> 00:18:51,456
Both of us. We both love golf.

278
00:19:06,511 --> 00:19:07,876
Rolfi!

279
00:19:07,946 --> 00:19:09,538
Stop it!

280
00:19:09,614 --> 00:19:11,276
Rolfi!

281
00:19:11,350 --> 00:19:13,011
Be quiet now!

282
00:19:14,486 --> 00:19:15,851
What's up?

283
00:19:15,921 --> 00:19:18,755
I don't know,
probably it's too hot for him too.

284
00:19:37,446 --> 00:19:39,437
I'll go and see.

285
00:19:53,130 --> 00:19:54,961
Brilliant!

286
00:19:55,032 --> 00:19:57,365
Like the difference
between day and night.

287
00:19:58,770 --> 00:20:00,260
Thanks very much.

288
00:20:00,338 --> 00:20:01,828
You're welcome.

289
00:20:03,509 --> 00:20:05,443
Where's Tom?

290
00:20:05,511 --> 00:20:07,672
- Who?
- Did you give him the eggs?

291
00:20:07,747 --> 00:20:09,271
Sorry?

292
00:20:12,819 --> 00:20:14,753
The driver is absolutely top-class.

293
00:20:14,821 --> 00:20:16,152
You must try it.

294
00:20:16,223 --> 00:20:17,383
Listen, young man.

295
00:20:17,457 --> 00:20:21,519
I don't know what game you're playing,
but I'm not going to join in.

296
00:20:23,831 --> 00:20:25,321
Will you go now, please?

297
00:20:29,471 --> 00:20:30,961
What game?

298
00:20:32,041 --> 00:20:33,674
Sorry, madam, but I don't understand

299
00:20:33,675 --> 00:20:35,307
why you're suddenly so unfriendly.

300
00:20:36,479 --> 00:20:40,142
Have Tom or I
done anything to annoy you?

301
00:20:40,216 --> 00:20:42,151
Please, would you leave?

302
00:20:43,754 --> 00:20:46,450
Did you behave badly while I was outside?

303
00:20:47,124 --> 00:20:49,059
Was he cheeky?

304
00:20:49,127 --> 00:20:51,994
- Did he say anything -
- That's enough.

305
00:20:53,799 --> 00:20:56,199
I asked you to leave, so...

306
00:20:56,268 --> 00:20:57,930
please go.

307
00:20:59,005 --> 00:21:00,165
Okay.

308
00:21:01,107 --> 00:21:04,566
I don't understand what's upset you so,
but if you insist...

309
00:21:04,645 --> 00:21:06,306
Fine.

310
00:21:08,282 --> 00:21:11,115
Give the eggs to Tom
and we won't bother you again.

311
00:21:11,185 --> 00:21:12,847
I'm sorry?

312
00:21:12,921 --> 00:21:15,412
Of course we'll be telling Eva and Fred.

313
00:21:15,490 --> 00:21:18,857
Honestly, I've never experienced
anything like it before.

314
00:21:19,528 --> 00:21:21,359
What about you, Tom?

315
00:21:25,534 --> 00:21:27,730
May we have the eggs now, please?

316
00:21:28,638 --> 00:21:30,970
I told you to leave!

317
00:21:31,041 --> 00:21:32,975
Did I do something wrong...

318
00:21:33,043 --> 00:21:35,035
Now just get out of here, you...

319
00:21:35,113 --> 00:21:37,104
Is the dog with you?
What's going on?

320
00:21:37,181 --> 00:21:39,342
- Get them out!
- Good to see you, Mr. Schober.

321
00:21:39,417 --> 00:21:40,907
You are Mr. Schober, right?

322
00:21:40,985 --> 00:21:42,977
Fred, I mean, Mr. Berlinger told me.

323
00:21:43,055 --> 00:21:45,353
What?
What's the matter?

324
00:21:45,424 --> 00:21:47,915
- Throw him out!
- Your wife's mistaken.

325
00:21:47,993 --> 00:21:49,654
I'm very glad you're here.

326
00:21:49,728 --> 00:21:51,890
I'm sure you can clarify
the misunderstanding.

327
00:21:51,965 --> 00:21:54,957
- Daddy, I can't -
- Please, Georg!

328
00:21:59,306 --> 00:22:01,900
It's outrageous!

329
00:22:02,910 --> 00:22:05,675
Can I explain how this
misunderstanding arose?

330
00:22:05,747 --> 00:22:08,910
Mrs. Berlinger sent me over
to fetch some eggs.

331
00:22:08,984 --> 00:22:10,474
So what? And then?

332
00:22:10,552 --> 00:22:13,886
Your wife gave the eggs to Peter,
but he smashed them.

333
00:22:13,956 --> 00:22:17,050
Yes. And she gave me
four more eggs, but...

334
00:22:17,126 --> 00:22:19,287
then the dog jumped up on me...

335
00:22:19,362 --> 00:22:20,853
and now...

336
00:22:20,931 --> 00:22:23,764
But it was a 12-pack,
and you're shopping Monday anyway...

337
00:22:23,834 --> 00:22:25,825
We just want the eggs,

338
00:22:25,903 --> 00:22:27,393
that's all.

339
00:22:28,071 --> 00:22:30,233
Can you tell me what's going on?

340
00:22:39,652 --> 00:22:41,142
Give them the eggs.

341
00:22:41,220 --> 00:22:43,382
Hold on!
Can you wait a moment?

342
00:22:43,456 --> 00:22:45,481
- Can I take them?
- Just a moment.

343
00:22:45,559 --> 00:22:47,220
What's going on?

344
00:22:47,294 --> 00:22:50,786
It can't just be about these ridiculous eggs.
Why this rage?

345
00:22:50,864 --> 00:22:53,356
I'm not justifying myself to these...

346
00:22:54,535 --> 00:22:58,164
I asked you to throw them out.
I must have my reasons.

347
00:23:00,509 --> 00:23:02,841
Do as you wish.
For me, the subject is closed.

348
00:23:02,911 --> 00:23:04,071
Anna?

349
00:23:08,451 --> 00:23:10,112
Would you please leave?

350
00:23:10,620 --> 00:23:12,781
My wife doesn't feel well.

351
00:23:15,459 --> 00:23:19,691
I can't act as arbitrator in a matter
I don't know anything about.

352
00:23:19,763 --> 00:23:21,424
Please, would you leave?

353
00:23:28,440 --> 00:23:29,931
What is it?

354
00:23:30,009 --> 00:23:31,499
If you don't mind?

355
00:23:33,679 --> 00:23:35,647
So give them to him!

356
00:23:35,715 --> 00:23:37,377
What's going on?

357
00:23:37,451 --> 00:23:39,442
Nothing's going on.

358
00:23:39,519 --> 00:23:42,852
She gave him the eggs,
the dog jumped on him, he smashed them.

359
00:23:42,923 --> 00:23:45,256
He wants more.
Is it so complicated?

360
00:23:45,326 --> 00:23:47,157
What kind of tone is that supposed to be?

361
00:23:47,829 --> 00:23:49,490
Watch I don't smash your balls as well!

362
00:23:53,502 --> 00:23:56,164
Now get out! Right now!

363
00:24:00,777 --> 00:24:02,267
Is it broken?

364
00:24:05,448 --> 00:24:07,781
Be good, now.

365
00:24:07,852 --> 00:24:09,342
Behave yourself!

366
00:24:12,456 --> 00:24:14,117
Be nice!

367
00:24:14,191 --> 00:24:16,183
I don't want to hurt you,
but behave yourself!

368
00:24:21,466 --> 00:24:23,401
Please stay where you are.

369
00:24:23,469 --> 00:24:24,959
Please stay there!

370
00:24:26,639 --> 00:24:29,335
- He hit me in the face.
- Yes. He started it.

371
00:24:31,178 --> 00:24:33,669
You can help him if you want,
but no messing about.

372
00:24:35,683 --> 00:24:37,845
- Bring him a chair.
- My knee!

373
00:24:37,919 --> 00:24:40,911
- He should take off his pants and sit down.
- A chair!

374
00:24:40,989 --> 00:24:43,480
Peter studies medicine. He'll fix it.

375
00:24:43,558 --> 00:24:45,720
Take off your pants, please.

376
00:24:56,039 --> 00:24:58,906
If you won't let me see your wound,
I can't help you.

377
00:24:59,009 --> 00:25:01,240
Sorry I hurt you,

378
00:25:01,279 --> 00:25:04,214
but you left me no choice,
you must admit.

379
00:25:05,383 --> 00:25:08,615
Be reasonable, Mr. Schober.
Let him look at your leg.

380
00:25:08,687 --> 00:25:10,518
He's sure to be able to help.

381
00:25:12,992 --> 00:25:14,653
Will you leave please?

382
00:25:14,727 --> 00:25:15,922
Please!

383
00:25:17,263 --> 00:25:18,924
This won't get us anywhere.

384
00:25:18,999 --> 00:25:21,832
You must let him help you.
You haven't any choice.

385
00:25:22,802 --> 00:25:24,794
You're a ship's captain, sir.

386
00:25:25,573 --> 00:25:28,872
You know that on board ship,
the Captain's word is final.

387
00:25:29,543 --> 00:25:31,535
So, what do you want to do, sir?

388
00:25:32,381 --> 00:25:35,043
Do you want to call someone?
An ambulance?

389
00:25:35,117 --> 00:25:36,607
Or the police?

390
00:25:37,352 --> 00:25:40,686
Go on! I won't stop you.
Nor will Tom.

391
00:25:40,757 --> 00:25:42,486
That's a promise!

392
00:25:42,558 --> 00:25:43,217
Right?

393
00:25:48,532 --> 00:25:50,193
What are you waiting for?

394
00:25:57,542 --> 00:26:00,102
He dropped the mobile in the water.

395
00:26:10,157 --> 00:26:11,818
Why are you doing this?

396
00:26:11,892 --> 00:26:13,382
Why not?

397
00:26:14,661 --> 00:26:16,754
Okay, then, another game.

398
00:26:17,432 --> 00:26:19,400
A guessing game.

399
00:26:20,768 --> 00:26:22,429
What's this?

400
00:26:37,187 --> 00:26:38,518
A golf ball.

401
00:26:38,588 --> 00:26:41,114
Exactly, sir, a golf ball.

402
00:26:42,193 --> 00:26:44,354
And why do I have it here in my pocket?

403
00:26:47,432 --> 00:26:49,366
The lady knows.

404
00:26:49,434 --> 00:26:51,095
Because...

405
00:26:54,206 --> 00:26:55,868
Well?

406
00:26:59,178 --> 00:27:00,008
Well?

407
00:27:01,280 --> 00:27:03,442
- Because you didn't hit it.
- Exactly!

408
00:27:03,517 --> 00:27:05,678
And why didn't I hit it?

409
00:27:05,752 --> 00:27:07,151
Because you were stopped.

410
00:27:07,221 --> 00:27:08,210
Exactly.

411
00:27:08,956 --> 00:27:10,788
And because I had to test
the club another way.

412
00:27:23,005 --> 00:27:25,030
Where is he?

413
00:27:25,107 --> 00:27:26,439
Cold.

414
00:27:28,345 --> 00:27:29,835
Cold.

415
00:27:30,580 --> 00:27:32,172
Colder.

416
00:27:34,685 --> 00:27:35,845
Cold.

417
00:27:53,273 --> 00:27:55,999
Warmer.

418
00:27:58,312 --> 00:28:00,473
Hotter.

419
00:28:00,548 --> 00:28:01,879
Cold.

420
00:28:22,940 --> 00:28:24,430
Really cold.

421
00:28:33,685 --> 00:28:35,847
Warmer, hotter, boiling!

422
00:29:00,048 --> 00:29:02,676
Would you kindly get me
some food from the kitchen?

423
00:29:03,852 --> 00:29:05,343
Would it be possible?

424
00:29:13,163 --> 00:29:15,654
Bananas or something like that.

425
00:29:18,002 --> 00:29:21,495
And don't think of picking up
a knife or something.

426
00:29:21,573 --> 00:29:23,404
I'd be sorry if you did.

427
00:29:23,475 --> 00:29:24,965
For your sake.

428
00:29:35,989 --> 00:29:38,480
The sun's coming out again.

429
00:29:43,164 --> 00:29:45,689
Very kind of you. Thank you.

430
00:30:01,384 --> 00:30:03,045
Hello! Sweetie!

431
00:30:07,024 --> 00:30:08,958
Where are you?

432
00:30:11,228 --> 00:30:13,390
Come on down!

433
00:30:14,733 --> 00:30:17,566
We're both thinking the same, aren't we?

434
00:30:22,909 --> 00:30:24,968
We saw your boat!

435
00:30:25,611 --> 00:30:28,512
Hello, Gerda!
Hello, Robert!

436
00:30:28,581 --> 00:30:31,244
How long have you been here?

437
00:30:31,318 --> 00:30:32,808
Not long.

438
00:30:32,886 --> 00:30:35,821
We're still unpacking.

439
00:30:35,889 --> 00:30:37,983
How long are you staying?

440
00:30:38,059 --> 00:30:39,890
A week or two.

441
00:30:39,961 --> 00:30:41,622
We're not sure yet.

442
00:30:41,696 --> 00:30:43,027
Great!

443
00:30:43,098 --> 00:30:45,863
- Hello, darling, lovely to see you.
- Hello.

444
00:30:51,942 --> 00:30:53,603
Have you met my sister?

445
00:30:53,677 --> 00:30:56,111
No! Pleased to meet you!

446
00:30:56,179 --> 00:30:57,339
Hello, Robert!

447
00:30:57,447 --> 00:30:59,143
- Everything okay?
- Of course.

448
00:31:01,619 --> 00:31:05,020
This is Paul.
He's living with our neighbors.

449
00:31:05,089 --> 00:31:07,422
- Hello, Paul!
- Hello, pleased to meet you!

450
00:31:07,493 --> 00:31:09,427
Are you cold?

451
00:31:09,495 --> 00:31:12,157
No, I have eczema.

452
00:31:12,231 --> 00:31:15,395
You should go swimming.
The water here does wonders for you.

453
00:31:15,468 --> 00:31:16,799
Thank you for the tip.

454
00:31:16,870 --> 00:31:18,235
Hello.

455
00:31:18,304 --> 00:31:19,271
How's Georg?

456
00:31:19,939 --> 00:31:21,497
Very well, thank you!

457
00:31:21,574 --> 00:31:23,065
So where is he?

458
00:31:23,144 --> 00:31:25,476
He pulled a muscle putting the mast up.

459
00:31:25,546 --> 00:31:27,036
So he's lying down.

460
00:31:27,114 --> 00:31:28,604
That's a real shame.

461
00:31:28,682 --> 00:31:30,844
That's the result of doing
everything yourself.

462
00:31:30,919 --> 00:31:33,320
Robert wouldn't dream of putting our boat

463
00:31:33,321 --> 00:31:35,253
in the water on his own, right?

464
00:31:37,092 --> 00:31:39,459
Tell your beloved to pull
himself together.

465
00:31:39,529 --> 00:31:42,521
We barbecue nearly every night.
We can't do without him.

466
00:31:42,598 --> 00:31:44,259
I'll tell him!

467
00:31:44,333 --> 00:31:47,667
I mean it. As soon as he's better,
come and see us right away.

468
00:31:47,738 --> 00:31:51,139
Robert's son is here with his girlfriend.
He'll like her.

469
00:31:51,975 --> 00:31:53,307
Right then.

470
00:31:54,612 --> 00:31:56,102
Have a good time, darling.

471
00:31:56,181 --> 00:31:58,513
If the wind doesn't change, bring the car.

472
00:31:58,616 --> 00:32:00,551
The weather forecast says wind.

473
00:32:00,586 --> 00:32:02,679
For tomorrow.

474
00:32:02,755 --> 00:32:05,417
- I said to Robert we'd get nowhere.
- Where are you moored?

475
00:32:05,491 --> 00:32:06,981
What?

476
00:32:07,059 --> 00:32:09,790
Oh! Over there,
behind the headland.

477
00:32:09,863 --> 00:32:11,023
But on the other side.

478
00:32:12,365 --> 00:32:15,198
- The wooden house covered in ivy?
- That's it.

479
00:32:15,268 --> 00:32:18,363
- It looks very pretty.
- Indeed it is, young man.

480
00:32:18,439 --> 00:32:20,270
Right then. Bye!

481
00:32:26,748 --> 00:32:29,308
- Are you staying all week?
- This week, sure.

482
00:32:33,490 --> 00:32:34,980
Might see you tonight!

483
00:32:35,058 --> 00:32:37,993
As you like.
We're always pleased to see you!

484
00:32:38,729 --> 00:32:40,390
I don't know yet.

485
00:32:40,464 --> 00:32:43,797
- We'll see how Georg is.
- Yes, you see! See you soon!

486
00:32:47,305 --> 00:32:49,967
They'll be here
in two hours at the latest...

487
00:32:50,041 --> 00:32:51,872
and then this farce will be over.

488
00:32:51,943 --> 00:32:53,775
Sorry, but that's not quite true.

489
00:32:53,846 --> 00:32:56,144
I heard the end of your phone call.

490
00:32:56,215 --> 00:33:00,151
You asked your friends to call you back
if they were coming tonight.

491
00:33:00,253 --> 00:33:01,744
Or did I misunderstand you?

492
00:33:01,788 --> 00:33:04,313
Even if they can't reach us,
they'll still come.

493
00:33:04,391 --> 00:33:06,018
Is lying allowed?

494
00:33:06,927 --> 00:33:08,417
Just a moment!

495
00:33:14,135 --> 00:33:15,625
There you are. Please.

496
00:33:16,972 --> 00:33:19,304
You really can speak to us openly.

497
00:33:19,375 --> 00:33:23,209
You'll feel much better.
We're also being very open with you.

498
00:33:27,884 --> 00:33:30,717
Perhaps try putting a cushion under it.

499
00:33:31,889 --> 00:33:34,915
If you'd accepted Peter's help,
it would be hurting less.

500
00:33:37,094 --> 00:33:39,255
I'm quite willing to help you.

501
00:33:39,331 --> 00:33:41,492
But I don't want to impose.

502
00:33:45,571 --> 00:33:47,199
Careful!

503
00:33:48,708 --> 00:33:51,734
Yes, raise the leg.
That's bound to be more comfortable.

504
00:33:55,416 --> 00:33:57,748
There we are! Done!

505
00:33:59,086 --> 00:34:00,917
Can you leave it out, you bastards?

506
00:34:02,624 --> 00:34:04,114
Is that an offer?

507
00:34:04,192 --> 00:34:05,682
- What?
- Using our first names?

508
00:34:11,534 --> 00:34:13,365
I'm very happy about that.

509
00:34:13,436 --> 00:34:16,371
It does vastly simplify our communication.

510
00:34:18,041 --> 00:34:20,703
I'd still like to apologize for just now,

511
00:34:20,777 --> 00:34:22,711
for being too familiar,

512
00:34:23,380 --> 00:34:25,568
but you must admit that the smack was

513
00:34:25,569 --> 00:34:27,875
an unreasonable reaction nonetheless.

514
00:34:30,755 --> 00:34:32,086
Paul.

515
00:34:35,894 --> 00:34:37,885
This is Peter.

516
00:34:39,431 --> 00:34:42,094
Come here, Tom.
Have you no manners?

517
00:34:42,168 --> 00:34:43,829
Give Georg your hand.

518
00:34:45,905 --> 00:34:47,566
Here, it's for the pain.

519
00:34:47,641 --> 00:34:50,167
What? To you, we're non-existent?

520
00:34:50,244 --> 00:34:52,576
- Being on familiar terms doesn't mean -
- You bastard...

521
00:35:09,532 --> 00:35:11,763
Quiet! Please!

522
00:35:11,835 --> 00:35:12,995
Stop!

523
00:35:15,172 --> 00:35:18,335
Stop it now, otherwise your mother
will get it, do you understand?

524
00:35:20,679 --> 00:35:21,668
Understand?

525
00:35:27,386 --> 00:35:29,047
Keep quiet now.

526
00:35:38,565 --> 00:35:41,227
What a scene,
just for being on first-name terms!

527
00:35:54,917 --> 00:35:57,284
We were only trying to improve relations.

528
00:35:58,188 --> 00:36:00,452
- I thought we could -
- Why are you doing that?

529
00:36:03,460 --> 00:36:05,122
Fatty, why are you doing that?

530
00:36:09,867 --> 00:36:11,357
Go on, tell us!

531
00:36:12,871 --> 00:36:15,931
I don't know. I...

532
00:36:16,007 --> 00:36:17,497
The Captain wants to know.

533
00:36:17,576 --> 00:36:18,406
Why?

534
00:36:19,746 --> 00:36:21,043
Well?

535
00:36:25,218 --> 00:36:27,779
It's difficult to talk about it. I...

536
00:36:27,855 --> 00:36:29,345
Don't be shy.

537
00:36:31,091 --> 00:36:33,059
