587
00:39:27,624 --> 00:39:29,922
isn't that enough for you?

588
00:39:29,993 --> 00:39:31,757
You get the message?

589
00:39:31,829 --> 00:39:33,990
Great!

590
00:39:34,932 --> 00:39:37,366
Fatty! He's got it!

591
00:39:39,071 --> 00:39:41,164
Now he knows everything!

592
00:39:42,674 --> 00:39:44,505
That's fantastic, really.

593
00:39:45,445 --> 00:39:46,776
Listen.

594
00:39:46,846 --> 00:39:48,336
Peter, come in here!

595
00:39:49,349 --> 00:39:51,715
Listen, we're going to bet, okay?

596
00:39:52,719 --> 00:39:54,381
Sit down, come on!

597
00:39:54,888 --> 00:39:57,550
- It's dark in here.
- Now don't fall asleep!

598
00:39:59,360 --> 00:40:01,522
We'll bet that -

599
00:40:01,596 --> 00:40:04,087
What's the time?

600
00:40:04,165 --> 00:40:06,030
Twenty to 9:00.

601
00:40:06,101 --> 00:40:08,935
That in, let's say, 12 hours...

602
00:40:09,005 --> 00:40:10,802
all three of you'll be kaput.

603
00:40:15,011 --> 00:40:16,240
What?

604
00:40:17,914 --> 00:40:19,939
You bet us, that tomorrow at 9:00,
you'll be alive,

605
00:40:20,017 --> 00:40:21,848
and we bet you,
you'll be dead, okay?

606
00:40:36,468 --> 00:40:37,662
They don't want to bet.

607
00:40:39,606 --> 00:40:41,540
That's no good. You have to bet.

608
00:40:42,308 --> 00:40:45,402
What do you think?
Do you think they've a chance of winning?

609
00:40:45,478 --> 00:40:47,743
You are on their side, aren't you?

610
00:40:47,815 --> 00:40:49,476
So, who will you bet with?

611
00:40:49,550 --> 00:40:51,211
What kind of bet is this?

612
00:40:51,285 --> 00:40:54,255
Dead, they can give nothing,
and conversely, they can win nothing.

613
00:40:54,322 --> 00:40:56,790
They'll lose in any case. Obviously.

614
00:40:56,858 --> 00:40:58,348
Stop this nonsense.

615
00:40:58,460 --> 00:41:00,655
Are you trying to scare us?

616
00:41:01,798 --> 00:41:03,823
Isn't what you've done already enough?

617
00:41:06,002 --> 00:41:07,492
What do you want? Our money?

618
00:41:07,570 --> 00:41:09,231
Help yourselves and get out.

619
00:41:11,575 --> 00:41:15,238
Don't you think Fred and Eva
might come and see what's going on?

620
00:41:15,312 --> 00:41:17,907
And give us a good hiding, right?

621
00:41:22,987 --> 00:41:24,147
Okay.

622
00:41:24,222 --> 00:41:25,713
As they say on TV:

623
00:41:25,791 --> 00:41:27,452
The bets are placed!

624
00:41:29,128 --> 00:41:31,460
And what'll we do now?

625
00:41:31,530 --> 00:41:34,329
Could you kindly make us some food?

626
00:41:35,001 --> 00:41:36,662
You worry me, Fatty.

627
00:41:37,337 --> 00:41:39,567
Can't you control yourself?

628
00:41:40,241 --> 00:41:42,573
You've just gobbled up the sausage.

629
00:41:43,744 --> 00:41:45,234
It's disgusting.

630
00:41:45,313 --> 00:41:46,803
What are these people going to think?

631
00:41:46,881 --> 00:41:48,713
I haven't eaten since lunchtime!

632
00:41:48,784 --> 00:41:50,684
And stop calling me Fatty.

633
00:41:50,752 --> 00:41:52,879
- Okay, Tom.
- Okay, Jerry.

634
00:41:54,990 --> 00:41:57,323
But can't you pay some attention
to your appearance?

635
00:41:57,994 --> 00:42:00,326
You think it makes you more attractive?

636
00:42:02,666 --> 00:42:04,327
Look at the Captain's wife.

637
00:42:05,236 --> 00:42:07,329
Do you think she finds you attractive?

638
00:42:08,305 --> 00:42:10,297
- With your flab?
- Stop it!

639
00:42:11,810 --> 00:42:13,607
Look at her.

640
00:42:13,678 --> 00:42:15,168
She's not as old as all that.

641
00:42:16,348 --> 00:42:17,838
Excuse me, madam.

642
00:42:19,285 --> 00:42:21,685
You'd be quite acceptable to her,

643
00:42:21,754 --> 00:42:23,915
but with that figure of yours!

644
00:42:24,690 --> 00:42:26,352
Follow her example.

645
00:42:26,426 --> 00:42:28,758
Her body's really in shape.

646
00:42:28,829 --> 00:42:30,524
Not a single extra calorie!

647
00:42:31,331 --> 00:42:33,163
I'm not so sure!

648
00:42:33,835 --> 00:42:35,234
What?

649
00:42:36,671 --> 00:42:39,037
Did you hear that, madam?

650
00:42:40,542 --> 00:42:42,204
That's really cheeky!

651
00:42:42,878 --> 00:42:45,244
We can't put up with that, can we?

652
00:42:53,857 --> 00:42:55,688
Hey you! Indian!

653
00:42:56,527 --> 00:42:58,188
What's your name anyway?

654
00:43:02,533 --> 00:43:03,967
Georg.

655
00:43:05,237 --> 00:43:06,727
Like Daddy.

656
00:43:06,805 --> 00:43:08,102
Lovely!

657
00:43:09,441 --> 00:43:11,774
Georgie-boy, come over to me.

658
00:43:13,346 --> 00:43:14,836
Come here.

659
00:43:20,154 --> 00:43:22,714
Come on. Sit down beside me.
We're going to play a game.

660
00:43:22,790 --> 00:43:23,779
Let the boy go!

661
00:43:25,159 --> 00:43:27,993
I know you don't want to play,
but you'll see, it's fun.

662
00:43:28,063 --> 00:43:29,724
Let the boy go!

663
00:43:31,700 --> 00:43:34,693
See how your mother's
standing up for you?

664
00:43:34,770 --> 00:43:37,705
- Dad could take an example from her!
- Stop it!

665
00:43:37,773 --> 00:43:40,435
For that we're going
to let your mom play with us.

666
00:43:41,677 --> 00:43:43,339
Hold Georgie a moment.

667
00:43:45,349 --> 00:43:48,341
We're playing a nice little game:
Kitten in the Bag.

668
00:43:50,355 --> 00:43:51,845
You'll see, it's fun.

669
00:43:54,859 --> 00:43:57,192
There! Don't panic! Nothing will happen.

670
00:43:57,296 --> 00:43:59,457
I said this is a nice game.

671
00:43:59,498 --> 00:44:00,988
A family game.

672
00:44:01,834 --> 00:44:04,963
Daddy is playing too
so he doesn't get bored.

673
00:44:05,038 --> 00:44:07,029
Right. Now listen!

674
00:44:07,707 --> 00:44:09,868
You'll have to keep still, or it's no fun.

675
00:44:11,211 --> 00:44:12,873
Hey! Listen now!

676
00:44:14,815 --> 00:44:16,305
That's right, Georgie.

677
00:44:17,151 --> 00:44:19,119
We'll work together, okay?

678
00:44:20,622 --> 00:44:22,598
The pillow case isn't uncomfortable, is it?

679
00:44:22,599 --> 00:44:24,114
You've enough air, haven't you?

680
00:44:26,628 --> 00:44:28,563
You've enough air, haven't you?

681
00:44:28,631 --> 00:44:29,461
Yes.

682
00:44:29,532 --> 00:44:31,227
Great. Then we can finally start.

683
00:44:31,901 --> 00:44:33,732
So, the starting point of our game

684
00:44:33,803 --> 00:44:37,968
was that mommy and our little Indian
wanted to slip out of here.

685
00:44:38,042 --> 00:44:40,010
- But why?
- Don't know.

686
00:44:40,077 --> 00:44:41,738
Is lying allowed, Fatty?

687
00:44:43,081 --> 00:44:45,743
What an example you're setting!
You know why.

688
00:44:45,817 --> 00:44:47,478
You mentioned her flab.

689
00:44:47,552 --> 00:44:48,951
What do you mean, me?

690
00:44:49,020 --> 00:44:51,182
It was you who doubted her flawlessness!

691
00:44:52,124 --> 00:44:54,058
Okay. Forget it!

692
00:44:54,126 --> 00:44:57,391
I understand too how it embarrassed her.
With the boy here.

693
00:44:57,496 --> 00:44:59,328
That's why we play
"Kitten in the Bag. "

694
00:44:59,366 --> 00:45:01,300
To preserve moral decency.

695
00:45:01,368 --> 00:45:05,361
The kiddy wears a pillow case
While mummy strips off, in great haste!

696
00:45:09,644 --> 00:45:12,135
We mustn't hurt the kitty cat, right?
Dad's broken leg is enough.

697
00:45:12,213 --> 00:45:14,045
Let the child go. Please!

698
00:45:14,116 --> 00:45:16,175
Exactly. Daddy's playing with us too.

699
00:45:21,825 --> 00:45:23,486
What are we waiting for?

700
00:45:26,496 --> 00:45:30,593
Tell your wife not to be so shy.
It's ridiculous.

701
00:45:30,668 --> 00:45:32,533
Anyway, I'm sure she isn't flabby.

702
00:45:34,205 --> 00:45:36,697
Please, let the child go.

703
00:45:37,542 --> 00:45:38,873
Please!

704
00:45:40,212 --> 00:45:42,737
You only have to say to her,
"Get undressed. "

705
00:45:44,684 --> 00:45:46,481
I beg you!

706
00:45:48,488 --> 00:45:50,319
"Get undressed, my darling. "

707
00:46:12,648 --> 00:46:14,138
Get undressed.

708
00:46:16,486 --> 00:46:18,647
"Get undressed, my darling. "

709
00:46:23,327 --> 00:46:25,488
Get undressed, my darling.

710
00:47:47,489 --> 00:47:48,421
Well done.

711
00:47:48,490 --> 00:47:51,186
What did I say? Not an ounce of flab.

712
00:47:51,260 --> 00:47:52,921
Now, let's get dressed again.

713
00:48:31,171 --> 00:48:33,834
Fatty, can you take the little piggy?

714
00:48:33,908 --> 00:48:36,069
He isn't quite potty-trained.

715
00:48:36,144 --> 00:48:37,975
Go and clean him up.

716
00:48:38,046 --> 00:48:40,709
- Let the child go!
- I won't do anything to him.

717
00:49:28,003 --> 00:49:29,664
Will you sit down, please?

718
00:49:33,009 --> 00:49:35,341
I'd advise you not to kick me.

719
00:49:47,858 --> 00:49:50,350
I hope you won't be
too bored with these two.

720
00:49:51,763 --> 00:49:53,890
Pour a pan of water over his head.

721
00:49:55,968 --> 00:49:58,459
But make sure you don't ruin the carpet.

722
00:50:27,070 --> 00:50:29,561
No, no, of course that was a joke.

723
00:50:29,639 --> 00:50:31,971
I have to retake Latin in the autumn.

724
00:50:32,041 --> 00:50:36,376
If I pass it, then things will get moving.
I'll study commercial law.

725
00:50:36,447 --> 00:50:38,608
But before that there's military service.

726
00:50:39,450 --> 00:50:41,111
Does it hurt a lot?

727
00:50:41,185 --> 00:50:42,847
Why don't you kill us right away?

728
00:50:43,521 --> 00:50:45,238
Don't forget the entertainment value.

729
00:50:45,239 --> 00:50:47,048
We'd all be deprived of our pleasure.

730
00:51:46,759 --> 00:51:48,989
Sorry about your leg.

731
00:51:49,061 --> 00:51:51,326
But it's your fault, if I might say so.

732
00:51:51,999 --> 00:51:53,830
Why did you smack Paul?

733
00:51:58,039 --> 00:52:01,031
For me, begging for the eggs
to no avail was very unpleasant.

734
00:52:02,210 --> 00:52:04,337
Humiliating, actually.

735
00:52:04,412 --> 00:52:06,074
I don't know if you realize that.

736
00:52:07,216 --> 00:52:09,548
It's just not worth it,

737
00:52:09,618 --> 00:52:12,109
all this charade, for a box of eggs.

738
00:52:15,892 --> 00:52:19,384
They should still be there.

739
00:52:19,462 --> 00:52:22,296
You should have trusted
what your wife said.

740
00:52:22,366 --> 00:52:26,029
She really begged you just
to let us leave with the eggs.

741
00:52:26,103 --> 00:52:28,265
Naturally one's always wiser
after the event.

742
00:52:30,175 --> 00:52:32,234
Ah! There they are!

743
00:52:34,746 --> 00:52:36,738
One of them is cracked.

744
00:52:36,816 --> 00:52:40,479
It's not bad, what these boxes withstand.
When you think-

745
00:52:41,254 --> 00:52:43,587
Why are you doing that?

746
00:52:43,657 --> 00:52:45,648
How stupid do you think I am?

747
00:52:45,726 --> 00:52:49,389
I don't understand. You're really
forcing me to treat you badly.

748
00:52:54,402 --> 00:52:57,064
Jesus! That's it! You've done it now!

749
00:53:00,109 --> 00:53:02,976
And Paul even said
we should take care of the carpet!

750
00:53:06,148 --> 00:53:08,140
Please, let us go!

751
00:53:11,955 --> 00:53:14,322
You're so young still!

752
00:53:16,394 --> 00:53:18,328
You have all your life before you!

753
00:53:21,065 --> 00:53:23,728
Nothing's happened yet!

754
00:53:25,237 --> 00:53:26,431
We'll say...

755
00:53:26,505 --> 00:53:29,532
that Georg broke his leg in the boat.

756
00:53:30,477 --> 00:53:32,809
- Everyone'll believe it, and -
- Please stop.

757
00:53:32,879 --> 00:53:34,540
Why are you humiliating yourself?

758
00:53:34,614 --> 00:53:36,673
It's just as unpleasant for me as for you.

759
00:54:14,478 --> 00:54:15,810
Georgie?

760
00:54:17,315 --> 00:54:18,805
Where are you?

761
00:55:44,330 --> 00:55:45,820
Georgie!

762
00:55:45,898 --> 00:55:47,389
I'm coming!

763
00:56:41,529 --> 00:56:43,690
Hold on,
I'll put on some music for us.

764
00:57:27,147 --> 00:57:29,081
Don't come any closer!

765
00:57:31,318 --> 00:57:33,047
The trigger!

766
00:57:35,056 --> 00:57:36,990
You have to prime the trigger!

767
00:57:53,843 --> 00:57:56,004
And you need to pull it too!

768
00:58:55,680 --> 00:58:57,842
Tralee trala, here we are!

769
00:58:59,184 --> 00:59:00,549
Mommy!

770
00:59:03,622 --> 00:59:05,215
Hello, my darling!

771
00:59:06,392 --> 00:59:08,417
Is everything okay?

772
00:59:12,533 --> 00:59:13,795
They've -

773
00:59:14,301 --> 00:59:16,735
They've killed Sissi!

774
00:59:17,404 --> 00:59:18,928
- Hi, Beavis!
- Hi, Butt-Head!

775
00:59:19,607 --> 00:59:21,872
- Everything under control?
- Looks like it.

776
00:59:24,779 --> 00:59:25,803
May I?

777
00:59:25,880 --> 00:59:27,541
Please. Sure.

778
00:59:28,718 --> 00:59:31,881
You must wonder, Captain,
where this lovely rifle comes from.

779
00:59:33,389 --> 00:59:34,947
Or does it seem familiar?

780
00:59:35,459 --> 00:59:37,654
Haven't you ever been hunting with Fred?

781
00:59:39,830 --> 00:59:42,994
Do you know, your little darling
just tried to kill me with it?

782
00:59:46,004 --> 00:59:50,168
Scarcely believable, but it's the truth,
and nothing but the truth.

783
00:59:50,241 --> 00:59:51,732
Isn't that right, Georgie?

784
00:59:56,849 --> 00:59:58,511
What do you say, Tom?

785
00:59:58,585 --> 00:59:59,916
Dreadful.

786
01:00:01,855 --> 01:00:03,516
What's the time?

787
01:00:03,590 --> 01:00:06,253
Just after 11:00.

788
01:00:06,327 --> 01:00:09,296
We should start thinking about our bet,
don't you think?

789
01:00:11,465 --> 01:00:15,129
Actually we ought to be grateful
to Georgie for helping us.

790
01:00:15,804 --> 01:00:17,135
One for Beavis,

791
01:00:17,205 --> 01:00:18,968
one for Butt-Head.

792
01:00:22,745 --> 01:00:25,646
A, B, BOO and out go you!

793
01:00:25,715 --> 01:00:30,176
You're not leaving at this stage.
First you'll have to say your age.

794
01:00:32,923 --> 01:00:34,254
Well?

795
01:00:37,829 --> 01:00:39,456
She doesn't want to play.

796
01:00:39,964 --> 01:00:42,057
Well, how old do you think she is?

797
01:00:44,070 --> 01:00:45,560
37?

798
01:00:47,573 --> 01:00:49,302
No flab...

799
01:00:49,809 --> 01:00:51,505
So I'd say,

800
01:00:51,578 --> 01:00:54,069
let's be generous,
let's say 35.

801
01:00:56,383 --> 01:00:57,315
Agreed?

802
01:01:00,154 --> 01:01:01,485
She agrees.

803
01:01:01,556 --> 01:01:03,547
Who are you going to start counting with?

804
01:01:04,258 --> 01:01:05,190
Her?

805
01:01:09,665 --> 01:01:12,156
And now I'm going to
get myself something to eat.

806
01:01:13,836 --> 01:01:15,498
One, two, three,

807
01:01:15,572 --> 01:01:17,665
four, five, six, seven...

808
01:01:34,192 --> 01:01:36,126
Can I get anyone anything?

809
01:02:12,803 --> 01:02:14,737
You're an idiot, Fatty.

810
01:02:14,805 --> 01:02:16,248
You don't shoot the person you've

811
01:02:16,249 --> 01:02:18,173
counted out, but the one that's left over!

812
01:02:18,242 --> 01:02:19,573
What's wrong with you?

813
01:02:19,644 --> 01:02:21,805
- He tried to escape!
- So what?

814
01:02:21,879 --> 01:02:24,041
That's no reason
to get trigger-happy.

815
01:02:24,116 --> 01:02:25,606
Have you no sense of timing?

816
01:02:26,452 --> 01:02:27,942
What's the time?

817
01:02:28,020 --> 01:02:29,783
Just before 12:00.

818
01:02:29,855 --> 01:02:31,346
Shit.

819
01:02:31,424 --> 01:02:33,085
We'll get nothing from the others now.

820
01:02:34,260 --> 01:02:37,093
- Let's get out of here.
- Fine.

821
01:02:37,163 --> 01:02:41,123
Thanks so much for the driver.
I'll put it back in the bag, okay?

822
01:02:41,202 --> 01:02:42,191
Thanks.

823
01:02:43,337 --> 01:02:44,827
So, have a good evening!

824
01:02:44,905 --> 01:02:46,237
Good-bye!

825
01:02:46,308 --> 01:02:47,605
Bye!

826
01:05:11,705 --> 01:05:13,639
They've gone.

827
01:05:51,016 --> 01:05:53,678
Do you hear? They've gone!

828
01:06:37,235 --> 01:06:39,726
I'll get a knife.

829
01:08:28,727 --> 01:08:30,753
Come on.
Calm down now.

830
01:08:36,236 --> 01:08:38,569
Take deep breaths.

831
01:08:42,142 --> 01:08:43,632
Come on, darling.

832
01:08:44,913 --> 01:08:46,574
Calm down now.

833
01:08:49,251 --> 01:08:51,082
Calm yourself.

834
01:08:53,589 --> 01:08:54,920
Calm yourself.

835
01:08:54,991 --> 01:08:57,824
That's it. Take some deep breaths.

836
01:10:52,823 --> 01:10:55,156
We've got to get out of here.

837
01:10:56,995 --> 01:10:59,054
What if they come back?

838
01:11:01,734 --> 01:11:04,168
Do you think you can walk
if I support you?

839
01:11:09,108 --> 01:11:10,599
I'll try.

840
01:11:20,455 --> 01:11:22,787
What's wrong with your arm?

841
01:11:28,564 --> 01:11:32,626
Shall I try and make a splint for it?
Then I can hold you better.

842
01:11:34,304 --> 01:11:36,465
No, it's okay. Come on.

843
01:12:01,434 --> 01:12:02,925
Let's go.

844
01:12:10,010 --> 01:12:11,501
Let's go.

845
01:12:21,290 --> 01:12:22,780
Okay?

846
01:12:32,803 --> 01:12:34,465
No! Anna!

847
01:12:36,508 --> 01:12:37,873
No!

848
01:13:25,129 --> 01:13:26,791
They've locked the door.

849
01:13:27,766 --> 01:13:29,597
We must use the window.

850
01:13:29,668 --> 01:13:31,158
I can't.

851
01:13:31,236 --> 01:13:32,726
Georg!

852
01:13:32,804 --> 01:13:35,137
- Please!
- I can't manage it.

853
01:13:35,208 --> 01:13:36,368
You go.

854
01:13:36,442 --> 01:13:39,934
It's crazy wasting so much time.
Run for it. Please!

855
01:13:40,012 --> 01:13:41,844
Climb out of the kitchen window.

856
01:13:41,915 --> 01:13:44,076
Try to get as far as the inn, or...

857
01:13:44,151 --> 01:13:46,642
If we're locked in here,
the gate will be shut too.

858
01:13:48,322 --> 01:13:50,257
That's true.

859
01:13:51,092 --> 01:13:53,754
Take a pair of pliers and cut the fence.

860
01:13:53,828 --> 01:13:57,765
But careful on the road.
Maybe they're waiting out there.

861
01:13:59,268 --> 01:14:01,293
Where are the pliers?

862
01:14:03,973 --> 01:14:06,067
I don't know.

863
01:14:06,142 --> 01:14:08,133
Here, in the kitchen.

864
01:14:10,146 --> 01:14:11,636
No,

865
01:14:11,715 --> 01:14:13,240
down at the boat shed.

866
01:14:14,452 --> 01:14:16,443
I can't leave you alone here.

867
01:14:16,520 --> 01:14:18,010
Go now, please!

868
01:14:19,357 --> 01:14:21,519
Put some clothes on.

869
01:14:21,593 --> 01:14:24,084
And shoes too, so you can run.

870
01:14:29,769 --> 01:14:31,930
Hold on, the bag's still here.

871
01:14:32,005 --> 01:14:33,495
Down there.

872
01:14:46,121 --> 01:14:48,055
I'll hide down in the wine cellar.

873
01:14:48,723 --> 01:14:50,555
The key must be in the door.

874
01:14:52,495 --> 01:14:55,328
I'll shut myself in
and wait for you to come back.

875
01:15:00,337 --> 01:15:02,669
How will you get down there?

876
01:15:02,739 --> 01:15:04,229
I'll manage.

877
01:15:20,459 --> 01:15:22,394
Go now! Please!

878
01:15:43,151 --> 01:15:45,086
The mobile! It's working again!

879
01:15:45,154 --> 01:15:46,086
What?

880
01:15:46,155 --> 01:15:48,646
It's working!
It's obviously dried out.

881
01:15:48,725 --> 01:15:50,886
- So get on the phone!
- Who to?

882
01:15:50,960 --> 01:15:53,452
Anyone! The police!

883
01:15:53,530 --> 01:15:55,191
What's their number?

884
01:15:55,265 --> 01:15:56,926
No idea.

885
01:15:57,034 --> 01:15:58,399
Call my mother...

886
01:15:58,435 --> 01:16:00,404
Your father-
No, wait...

887
01:16:00,472 --> 01:16:03,134
Call Peter, he's at home,
I know, he wanted to -

888
01:16:03,208 --> 01:16:05,870
Press four and then hit speed-dial.

889
01:16:08,714 --> 01:16:10,204
It's not ringing.

890
01:16:12,718 --> 01:16:14,208
Let me listen.

891
01:16:17,391 --> 01:16:18,722
But there is a signal!

892
01:16:18,792 --> 01:16:20,953
Some of the contacts
are probably still damp.

893
01:16:39,983 --> 01:16:40,972
Nothing.

894
01:16:43,153 --> 01:16:45,816
Get the hair dryer.
Maybe it'll help.

895
01:16:46,657 --> 01:16:48,818
Can you pass me the chair?

896
01:17:15,623 --> 01:17:17,454
It won't work.

897
01:19:01,275 --> 01:19:02,766
Leave it, come on.

898
01:19:04,112 --> 01:19:06,012
Maybe it's permanently broken.

899
01:19:06,081 --> 01:19:07,571
Get going!

900
01:19:10,253 --> 01:19:13,745
We're wasting far too much time.
Let me do it.

901
01:19:16,092 --> 01:19:17,924
Go on!

902
01:19:20,431 --> 01:19:22,592
Pull me over there on the chair.

903
01:19:22,666 --> 01:19:25,158
I think it'll be easier than walking.

904
01:19:57,840 --> 01:19:59,034
Thanks.

905
01:20:00,509 --> 01:20:02,443
And now, run!

906
01:20:15,026 --> 01:20:16,994
Please, forgive me!

907
01:20:24,202 --> 01:20:25,794
It -

908
01:20:36,884 --> 01:20:38,875
I love you!

909
01:20:48,063 --> 01:20:49,554
Run, please!

910
01:22:45,729 --> 01:22:47,890
Help!

911
01:23:20,201 --> 01:23:22,693
Peter? It's Georg!

912
01:23:24,206 --> 01:23:27,141
Can you hear me?
I can barely hear you!

913
01:23:28,978 --> 01:23:31,641
Listen, if you can hear me,

914
01:23:31,715 --> 01:23:34,582
send the police over to our
lake house, right away!

915
01:23:36,319 --> 01:23:37,582
Hello?

916
01:23:38,089 --> 01:23:39,954
Shit!

917
01:23:51,737 --> 01:23:53,672
Peter! Can you hear me?

918
01:26:01,183 --> 01:26:02,344
Stop!

919
01:28:15,702 --> 01:28:17,192
Missed!

920
01:28:17,270 --> 01:28:18,760
Morning, Captain.

921
01:28:20,408 --> 01:28:21,898
Morning.

922
01:28:21,976 --> 01:28:24,809
They'll be there any minute.

923
01:28:24,879 --> 01:28:27,872
We'll have to hurry then.
Right, Beavis?

924
01:28:27,950 --> 01:28:29,781
Why don't you believe me?

925
01:28:29,851 --> 01:28:33,048
- How old did we say? 37?
- 35.

926
01:28:33,121 --> 01:28:37,183
Good that the battery
charger's in the car!

927
01:28:37,260 --> 01:28:39,694
- If it's her age, you must start with her.
- Why?

928
01:28:39,762 --> 01:28:41,593
- The battery was okay.
- That's the rules.

929
01:28:41,664 --> 01:28:43,496
Okay, I'll start with her.

930
01:28:43,567 --> 01:28:45,899
Yes, I know.

931
01:28:45,970 --> 01:28:49,907
It's time you had another idea.
The lady tried that trick before.

932
01:28:49,975 --> 01:28:51,465
Count faster, Beavis.

933
01:28:53,144 --> 01:28:55,237
Do you think we have no imagination?

934
01:28:55,313 --> 01:28:58,147
Without risk, you can't have a bet,
that's obvious, Captain.

935
01:28:58,251 --> 01:29:00,185
You must have a chance too.

936
01:29:00,219 --> 01:29:02,136
The wind blows where it wishes.

937
01:29:02,137 --> 01:29:04,919
That's the joy of sailing, don't you think?

938
01:29:04,992 --> 01:29:06,323
Right then!

939
01:29:06,393 --> 01:29:07,883
...thirty-four, thirty-five!

940
01:29:07,961 --> 01:29:10,122
Don't make the same mistake again.

941
01:29:10,197 --> 01:29:12,180
It's the one that's left who's turn it is,

942
01:29:12,181 --> 01:29:13,690
not the one who's counted out.

943
01:29:19,307 --> 01:29:20,240
Hang on.

944
01:29:20,309 --> 01:29:22,971
I can see a new toy.

945
01:29:23,712 --> 01:29:25,771
I assume we owe this to the lady?

946
01:29:27,951 --> 01:29:30,613
This will make things a bit more amusing.

947
01:29:32,289 --> 01:29:34,553
The dumb suffer in unspectacular fashion.

948
01:29:36,227 --> 01:29:38,058
We want to offer the audience something...

949
01:29:38,129 --> 01:29:40,188
and show what we can do, right?

950
01:29:49,408 --> 01:29:51,240
You can join in again now.

951
01:29:54,914 --> 01:29:57,405
We were already
on first-name terms, right?

952
01:29:58,919 --> 01:30:00,580
So, Anna,

953
01:30:01,488 --> 01:30:03,012
now we're going to play:

954
01:30:03,090 --> 01:30:05,524
"The Loving Wife", or...

955
01:30:05,592 --> 01:30:07,474
Whether by knife or whether by gun

956
01:30:07,475 --> 01:30:09,689
Losing your life can sometimes be fun.

957
01:30:13,034 --> 01:30:14,696
Hey! No falling asleep!

958
01:30:15,371 --> 01:30:18,568
You have to play with us,
or you'll be gagged again.

959
01:30:18,641 --> 01:30:20,472
That's not very nice, is it?

960
01:30:23,413 --> 01:30:26,576
So, here are the rules of the game:

961
01:30:26,650 --> 01:30:29,848
Georgie senior has been counted out,
so it's his turn.

962
01:30:31,189 --> 01:30:32,850
It'll be hard to change that.

963
01:30:33,691 --> 01:30:35,852
Unless you want to take his place.

964
01:30:37,029 --> 01:30:38,519
Do you want to?

965
01:30:41,066 --> 01:30:44,332
I'm sure Fatty will understand.
Right, Fatty?

966
01:30:44,404 --> 01:30:46,065
Don't call me Fatty.

967
01:30:46,139 --> 01:30:50,473
- You see, he understands.
- Get this over with. That's enough.

968
01:30:50,543 --> 01:30:52,205
That's enough?

969
01:30:52,279 --> 01:30:53,940
You think that's enough?

970
01:30:55,816 --> 01:30:57,477
What do you think, Anna?

971
01:30:57,585 --> 01:30:59,918
Have you had enough?
Or do you want to play some more?

972
01:31:00,722 --> 01:31:02,314
Don't reply anymore.

973
01:31:02,391 --> 01:31:04,723
Let them do what they want. Please!

974
01:31:04,793 --> 01:31:06,955
Then it'll be over quicker.

975
01:31:07,029 --> 01:31:09,190
Huh, that's cowardly!

976
01:31:09,265 --> 01:31:12,098
We're not up to feature film length yet.

977
01:31:12,168 --> 01:31:14,102
Is that enough?

978
01:31:14,170 --> 01:31:15,595
But you want a real ending,

979
01:31:15,596 --> 01:31:17,971
with plausible plot development, don't you?

980
01:31:18,041 --> 01:31:21,670
The bet is still on.
It can't be withdrawn unilaterally.

981
01:31:22,347 --> 01:31:23,439
So:

982
01:31:23,515 --> 01:31:25,915
the game is called: "The Loving Wife. "

983
01:31:25,984 --> 01:31:29,317
Although Beavis has done the counting,
she can choose...

984
01:31:29,387 --> 01:31:31,879
who will be next. And...

985
01:31:31,957 --> 01:31:33,618
using what implement!

986
01:31:34,293 --> 01:31:36,454
Do we prefer the little knife?

987
01:31:36,529 --> 01:31:38,361
Or the rifle?

988
01:31:39,599 --> 01:31:41,760
Well then, what does the housewife say?

989
01:31:46,274 --> 01:31:48,265
Hello, wakey, wakey!

990
01:31:50,978 --> 01:31:53,914
So, you're not interested?

991
01:31:53,982 --> 01:31:56,075
You don't want to play anymore.

992
01:31:57,186 --> 01:31:59,347
Beavis, show her the game again.

993
01:31:59,421 --> 01:32:00,616
Wait.

994
01:32:00,690 --> 01:32:02,021
Here you are.

995
01:32:02,091 --> 01:32:03,581
Hey, careful!

996
01:32:03,660 --> 01:32:05,321
I almost cut myself.

997
01:32:05,395 --> 01:32:06,885
Really?

998
01:32:17,943 --> 01:32:21,106
You see. It's the little knife.
You can spare him that.

999
01:32:21,179 --> 01:32:23,011
You only have to play with us.

1000
01:32:26,118 --> 01:32:27,779
I understand, Anna.

1001
01:32:27,854 --> 01:32:29,344
I understand, really!

1002
01:32:30,356 --> 01:32:33,520
It's not a good feeling,
causing the one you love to suffer.

1003
01:32:35,195 --> 01:32:38,256
But it costs so little to avoid all that.

1004
01:32:38,333 --> 01:32:41,825
You only need follow the rules,
and all will be well.

1005
01:33:08,800 --> 01:33:09,892
What must I do?

1006
01:33:12,938 --> 01:33:15,099
You see, it wasn't that difficult.

1007
01:33:15,774 --> 01:33:17,538
And we'll make it easy too.

1008
01:33:17,610 --> 01:33:19,771
You recite a prayer of your choice.

1009
01:33:19,846 --> 01:33:22,343
If you say it flawlessly, God will help you

1010
01:33:22,344 --> 01:33:24,375
and you choose what happens next.

1011
01:33:30,224 --> 01:33:32,557
Or shall we carry on with Georgie senior?

1012
01:33:34,296 --> 01:33:35,320
I don't know a prayer.

1013
01:33:36,998 --> 01:33:38,659
You don't know any prayers?

1014
01:33:39,569 --> 01:33:41,469
Not a single prayer?

1015
01:33:43,906 --> 01:33:44,895
Is that possible?

1016
01:33:46,075 --> 01:33:47,566
Tell her one, Fatty.

1017
01:33:47,644 --> 01:33:49,669
Stop calling me Fatty all the time.

1018
01:33:49,746 --> 01:33:51,737
I'll stop saying it. Well?

1019
01:33:53,684 --> 01:33:56,153
Oh Lord and Father, make me kind,
So I, in heaven, my place may find.

1020
01:33:56,220 --> 01:33:59,246
- That's too easy.
- I can't think of any others.

1021
01:34:00,425 --> 01:34:01,585
Okay.

1022
01:34:01,659 --> 01:34:04,322
Oh Lord and Father, make me kind,
So I, in heaven, my place may find.

1023
01:34:06,332 --> 01:34:08,266
No! Not like that!

1024
01:34:08,334 --> 01:34:09,825
It's a prayer.

1025
01:34:09,903 --> 01:34:12,497
You can't just drone on like that.

1026
01:34:12,572 --> 01:34:15,735
You're asking the Lord God for something.
So pray properly.

1027
01:34:17,612 --> 01:34:20,080
Go on.
Go down on your knees properly.

1028
01:34:21,415 --> 01:34:23,508
Go on! Get on with it!

1029
01:34:28,857 --> 01:34:31,621
There. That's right. Kneel down properly.

1030
01:34:34,130 --> 01:34:36,064
Put your hands together.

1031
01:34:36,733 --> 01:34:38,564
Not on your stomach.

1032
01:34:38,635 --> 01:34:41,298
Where is the one you pray to?
Up there!

1033
01:34:42,206 --> 01:34:44,970
You have to pray to the heavens!
That's it!

1034
01:34:46,577 --> 01:34:50,241
Right, and now, in a fervent tone,
if you don't mind.

1035
01:34:56,455 --> 01:34:59,288
- Beavis, can you help her a little?
- No!

1036
01:35:07,934 --> 01:35:10,095
Oh Lord and Father, make me kind,

1037
01:35:12,607 --> 01:35:14,438
So I, in heaven, my place may find.

1038
01:35:14,509 --> 01:35:15,976
Well done!
You did that well!

1039
01:35:17,311 --> 01:35:20,804
That was the trial run,
and now we're going for Olympic Gold:

1040
01:35:20,883 --> 01:35:24,216
If you can recite this prayer,
which is sadly much too short,

1041
01:35:24,286 --> 01:35:26,949
from back to front, without any mistakes,

1042
01:35:27,023 --> 01:35:31,323
you can not only choose
which of you kicks the bucket first,

1043
01:35:31,394 --> 01:35:35,661
but also, and no doubt
this will interest you more - how.

1044
01:35:35,733 --> 01:35:39,999
whether quick and painless by the bullet...

1045
01:35:40,071 --> 01:35:41,539
Careful!

1046
01:35:48,013 --> 01:35:49,982
Where's the remote?

1047
01:35:51,184 --> 01:35:53,516
Where's the fucking remote control?

1048
01:36:19,783 --> 01:36:22,946
That was the trial run,
and now we're going for Olympic Gold:

1049
01:36:23,019 --> 01:36:26,853
If you can recite this prayer,
which is sadly much too short,

1050
01:36:26,923 --> 01:36:30,587
from back to front, without any mistakes,

1051
01:36:30,661 --> 01:36:33,653
you can not only choose
which of you kicks the bucket first,

1052
01:36:33,731 --> 01:36:38,066
but also, and no doubt
this will interest you more - how:

1053
01:36:38,137 --> 01:36:40,970
whether quick and painless by the bul -

1054
01:36:44,711 --> 01:36:48,545
You shouldn't have done that, Anna.
One doesn't break the rules.

1055
01:36:48,615 --> 01:36:51,449
Sorry. You've failed.

1056
01:36:54,822 --> 01:36:57,313
Say good-bye to Georgie.

1057
01:37:32,298 --> 01:37:34,289
Would you sit down?

1058
01:38:14,746 --> 01:38:16,236
Can you give me your gloves?

1059
01:38:21,386 --> 01:38:23,878
...only it's all inverted.

1060
01:38:23,956 --> 01:38:27,414
But of course all these predictions are wrong
so as to avoid a panic.

1061
01:38:27,493 --> 01:38:28,983
But now Kelvin knows how it really is...

1062
01:38:29,062 --> 01:38:32,225
and wants to warn his wife
and daughter in time.

1063
01:38:32,299 --> 01:38:34,114
But the problem is not only getting

1064
01:38:34,115 --> 01:38:36,292
from the world of antimatter to reality,

1065
01:38:36,370 --> 01:38:37,895
- but also to regain communication -
- Look!

1066
01:38:39,240 --> 01:38:40,935
Now that's a sporting attitude!

1067
01:38:45,147 --> 01:38:46,978
Hey, look out, fatso!

1068
01:38:47,049 --> 01:38:48,539
I thought you were a non-swimmer.

1069
01:38:56,893 --> 01:38:59,054
Go and get the widow.
She'll feel lonely otherwise.

1070
01:39:02,867 --> 01:39:04,528
Would you mind cooperating?

1071
01:39:04,602 --> 01:39:07,572
It's not easy.
Otherwise I might hurt you.

1072
01:39:13,078 --> 01:39:15,013
So. Where was I?

1073
01:39:15,081 --> 01:39:18,573
The communication problems
between matter and antimatter.

1074
01:39:18,651 --> 01:39:21,313
Exactly. As if you were in a black hole!

1075
01:39:21,387 --> 01:39:25,222
Gravitation is so strong that nothing
can escape it: absolute silence.

1076
01:39:25,292 --> 01:39:26,953
- By the way, what's the time?
- What?

1077
01:39:27,027 --> 01:39:28,517
What's the time?

1078
01:39:28,595 --> 01:39:30,086
Just after eight.

1079
01:39:30,165 --> 01:39:31,154
Already?

1080
01:39:38,140 --> 01:39:39,300
Why?

1081
01:39:39,375 --> 01:39:42,538
The deadline was at 9:00.
She had almost an hour left!

1082
01:39:42,611 --> 01:39:45,079
Firstly,
it was too hard to sail like that,

1083
01:39:45,147 --> 01:39:49,642
- and secondly, I'm starting to get hungry.
- That's true.

1084
01:40:03,002 --> 01:40:04,993
...when Kelvin overcomes gravitation,

1085
01:40:05,070 --> 01:40:07,402
it turns out that one universe is real,

1086
01:40:07,473 --> 01:40:09,635
but the other is just a fiction.

1087
01:40:09,709 --> 01:40:11,074
How does that happen?

1088
01:40:11,144 --> 01:40:14,477
What do I know! It was a kind of
model projection in cyberspace.

1089
01:40:14,547 --> 01:40:17,881
And where is your hero now?
In reality or fiction?

1090
01:40:17,952 --> 01:40:20,443
His family is in reality
and he's in fiction.

1091
01:40:20,521 --> 01:40:23,685
- But the fiction is real, isn't it?
- How do you mean?

1092
01:40:23,759 --> 01:40:26,751
- Well, you see it in the film, right?
- Of course.

1093
01:40:26,828 --> 01:40:30,127
So, it's just as real as the reality
which you see likewise, right?

1094
01:40:30,198 --> 01:40:31,325
- Crap.
- Why?

1095
01:40:59,899 --> 01:41:02,232
Is anyone awake yet?

1096
01:41:09,343 --> 01:41:10,833
Who is it?

1097
01:41:18,187 --> 01:41:19,347
Good morning to you.

1098
01:41:19,421 --> 01:41:21,912
Sorry to disturb you so early,
but I've come from Anna's.

1099
01:41:21,990 --> 01:41:23,480
And?

1100
01:41:24,828 --> 01:41:26,489
Don't you remember me?

1101
01:41:26,563 --> 01:41:29,225
Yesterday afternoon, on the jetty.
I'm Paul.

1102
01:41:29,299 --> 01:41:30,789
Oh, yes.

1103
01:41:32,001 --> 01:41:33,833
- Good morning.
- Morning.

1104
01:41:33,904 --> 01:41:37,237
Anna sent me. We had guests arrive
unexpectedly this morning...

1105
01:41:37,308 --> 01:41:40,301
and she wonders if
you could spare her a few eggs?

1106
01:41:40,378 --> 01:41:41,868
I think so.

1107
01:41:41,947 --> 01:41:43,437
Come in.

1108
01:41:43,515 --> 01:41:45,676
Wait a minute.